modules.description: Inspects JSX elements by extracting their tag, attributes, and child nodes through a pattern-matching interface. Works with HTML element representations derived from JSX syntax. Used to debug rendered structures by analyzing their composition during runtime.

Checks if a string represents a self-closing HTML tag, determines if a string is an HTML or SVG element, and safely appends escaped text to a buffer for HTML output. Works with strings and buffer structures. Used to validate tags and generate safe HTML content during internal rendering processes.

Generates HTML from JSX-like syntax using element construction functions and a rendering function that outputs strings. It works with custom element types and attributes to build structured markup. Used to dynamically create HTML content in web applications written with OCaml or Reason.

Extracts and analyzes JSX element structures, enabling runtime inspection of tags, attributes, and children through pattern matching. Provides utilities to validate HTML/SVG tags, check for self-closing elements, and safely append escaped text to buffers. These functions support debugging and safe HTML generation during rendering. For example, it can identify a `<div>` tag, verify if a string is a valid SVG element, or append text without introducing XSS vulnerabilities.
